Looks fantastic. It did take a few minutes to get forked over and modify for location, °F instead of °C, etc. Perhaps a future version could use a config.js or something that would just swap those.<p>For the record, you want to edit <i>js/scripts/controllers.js</i> and <i>js/scripts/view/dashboard.html</i>.<p>Replacing Helsinki in the <i>openweathermap.org</i> link with your plain text city name seems to work.<p>For Fahrenheit, replace the &quot;var temp&quot; line in <i>controllers.js</i> with:<p><pre><code>    var temp = Math.round(((parseInt(data.main.temp) - 273.15) * 9/5) + 32, 2) + &quot;°F&quot;;
</code></pre>
I didn&#x27;t get the github.io pages working in less than a few minutes, so I just grabbed it locally where it&#x27;ll probably work faster anyway. Thanks also for the great plugin link. Excellent work Jakke, beautiful typography.
